{{Quote|Those causing the Reslian Purge believed someday a Man-Hutt would sweep evil from the Galaxy.|Soontir Fel|<ref name="X-Wing Rogue Squadron 25">[[X-Wing Rogue Squadron 25|''X-Wing Rogue Squadron'' 25]]</ref>}}
The '''Lortan Fanatics''', also called the '''[[Kopa Khan]] cultists''' in the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] propaganda,<ref name="EGW10">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-guide-to-warfare-authors-cut-part-10-the-rise-of-the-empire|series=Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Warfare Author's Cut|text=Part 10: The Rise of the Empire}}</ref> were a group of warlike beings from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Lorta/Legends|Lorta]]. They embarked on a crusade against the [[Tunroth]], nearly exterminating that [[Species/Legends|species]] until they were stopped by Imperial intervention in [[6 BBY/Legends|6 BBY]]. As a result the [[Lortan]] Fanatics were exterminated in turn; [[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]], as part of the [[37th Imperial Fighter Wing]], battled against their remnants.

